WEBVTT

02:17.560 --> 02:20.564
Come on, Laurie Anne. It's going to storm.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.081
Hi.

03:05.480 --> 03:07.448
Laurie Anne?

03:11.040 --> 03:13.964
Honey? Don't scare Mama now.

03:27.960 --> 03:30.486
Excuse me. Move along.

03:31.280 --> 03:32.691
Mmm-hmm.

03:46.280 --> 03:48.931
Chief's going to have a cow
when he sees you nosing around, Mike.

03:49.120 --> 03:51.441
I won't tell him if you don't.
What you got, Sam?

03:51.600 --> 03:54.001
There's not much left.
Just like the last time.

03:54.160 --> 03:56.162
- Anybody see anything?
- The mother said she saw...

03:56.320 --> 03:58.288
I thought I told you
to stay out of this, Hanlon.

03:58.440 --> 04:00.283
I'm just a concerned citizen, Chief.

04:00.440 --> 04:03.808
And I call six kids missing or dead
a major cause for alarm here.

04:03.960 --> 04:06.201
It may be just a rash of runaways.
Kids get itchy feet.

04:06.360 --> 04:08.886
Right. A five-year-old in a toy car
gets itchy feet.

04:09.040 --> 04:11.691
What, a seven-year-old trots down
to Acapulco for a wild weekend?

04:11.840 --> 04:14.161
The boy's father took him.
The other one...

04:14.840 --> 04:18.845
Chief, there's something terribly wrong
here in Derry. And you know it.

04:19.960 --> 04:22.804
Hey. I'm the cop. You're the librarian.

04:22.960 --> 04:23.961
Okay?

04:47.800 --> 04:48.847
Georgie.

04:54.720 --> 04:56.051
<i>May 28th.</i>

04:56.320 --> 04:57.890
<i>Another killing today.</i>

04:58.600 --> 05:02.525
<i>But this time, there was something more.
Something that makes my skin crawl.</i>

05:03.680 --> 05:06.490
<i>A picture that shouldn't...
No, no, that couldn't have been there.</i>

05:07.400 --> 05:09.607
<i>It's time to tell the others
what's happening.</i>

05:09.760 --> 05:11.569
<i>I can't put it off any longer.</i>

05:12.040 --> 05:13.451
<i>But I hope I'm wrong.</i>

05:14.400 --> 05:16.243
<i>Oh, I hope to God I'm wrong.</i>

05:32.560 --> 05:35.928
<i>Taggert steps onto the moors
as the fog curls around his ankles.</i>

05:36.080 --> 05:39.448
<i>He shivers, buttons his coat,
and walks on, disappearing into the mist.</i>

05:39.600 --> 05:41.364
<i>A shadowy figure lurches into frame,</i>

05:41.520 --> 05:44.126
<i>dripping with foul water
and dark oozing mud.</i>

05:45.120 --> 05:47.441
Yeah. Yeah.

05:48.960 --> 05:50.928
Bill, for the last time.

05:51.120 --> 05:52.121
In a minute!

05:52.440 --> 05:54.363
That's what you said a half an hour ago.

05:54.520 --> 05:57.046
<i>- And a half hour before that.</i>
- Okay!

05:58.560 --> 05:59.561
Okay.

06:03.040 --> 06:04.804
- It's cold.
- Sorry.

06:05.600 --> 06:08.046
I like the changes, Bill.
They're wonderful.

06:08.320 --> 06:11.802
- I wish you'd tell that idiot, Greco.
- I do. Every day.

06:12.800 --> 06:14.802
You didn't have to
take this job, you know.

06:14.960 --> 06:16.291
It's not as if we need the money.

06:16.480 --> 06:19.290
In case you've forgotten,
I took the job to be with you.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.367
Besides, if they're gonna hire somebody
to mangle one of my books,

06:22.520 --> 06:23.521
it might as well be me.

06:23.760 --> 06:26.843
Of course, the idea of actually taking
a vacation didn't even occur...

06:27.000 --> 06:28.729
So I could hang around the set
with a bunch of actors?

06:28.880 --> 06:31.281
That's not what I do, Audra.
Writing is what I do.

06:31.440 --> 06:33.920
At least when you're doing a novel,
you're in a good mood.

06:34.360 --> 06:36.647
Audra, could we...

06:38.560 --> 06:40.642
I'm asleep, unless it's Greco.

06:41.640 --> 06:42.641
Greco.

06:43.320 --> 06:44.481
Greco.

06:46.440 --> 06:47.441
Yeah?

06:47.600 --> 06:50.683
<i>Bill, is that you?</i>
- Sorry, fella, do I know you?

06:50.960 --> 06:53.440
<i>This is Mike Hanlon, Bill, from Derry.</i>

06:55.080 --> 06:56.411
<i>Swear to me.</i>

06:57.000 --> 06:59.128
Swear to me that if it isn't dead,

07:01.280 --> 07:03.009
we'll all come back.

07:06.240 --> 07:09.608
- Sorry, Mike, for a minute there...
<i>- You didn't know who I was.</i>

07:10.640 --> 07:12.324
For a minute there, I didn't.

07:13.120 --> 07:14.121
<i>Bill,</i>

07:15.360 --> 07:16.566
<i>It's back.</i>

07:17.320 --> 07:19.971
You're... Sure?

07:20.520 --> 07:24.525
<i>Yeah. I found a photograph of George.</i>

07:26.800 --> 07:27.801
George?

07:35.040 --> 07:36.041
What is it?

07:36.720 --> 07:38.210
Who was on the phone?

07:39.200 --> 07:42.204
Nobody. Wrong number.

07:43.760 --> 07:44.761
Bill?

07:47.000 --> 07:48.968
I have to go back to work.

07:49.840 --> 07:50.841
Bill?

07:55.960 --> 07:57.485
Georgie.

08:22.160 --> 08:24.686
Please, Bill. Tell me a story.

08:25.120 --> 08:26.963
Maybe later.

08:27.280 --> 08:29.123
The magic stone story.

08:29.480 --> 08:31.801
Please, Bill. Please.

08:32.440 --> 08:36.081
Go bug somebody else, you little cootie.
I don't feel so hot.

08:37.200 --> 08:38.201
Georgie?

08:41.680 --> 08:44.650
For me? You made it for me?

08:45.560 --> 08:47.005
Can I go sail it?

08:47.360 --> 08:52.366
Oh, well, you have to seal it
first with paraffin.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.482
- What's that? Where is it?
- It's in the cellar.

09:31.640 --> 09:35.247
I wish you could come, too.
She's your boat, really.

09:35.480 --> 09:36.481
Thanks, Bill.

09:38.320 --> 09:41.847
Yuck. You got cooties all over me.

09:46.720 --> 09:47.881
Uh, Georgie.

09:48.440 --> 09:51.011
Don't stay out too long,
or Mom will have a bird.

09:51.560 --> 09:54.086
- I won't.
- Georgie.

09:59.000 --> 10:00.001
Be careful.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.525
Sure. Sure, I will.

10:09.040 --> 10:11.520
SS Georgie!

10:15.040 --> 10:16.326
Come on, come on!

10:32.560 --> 10:34.722
<i>SS Georgie,</i> out of the way!

10:46.040 --> 10:47.246
No, please, no!

10:57.480 --> 10:59.164
<i>Hi, Georgie.</i>

11:02.880 --> 11:04.962
Aren't you going to say hello?

11:07.560 --> 11:08.686
Oh.

11:08.920 --> 11:10.763
Come on, bucko.

11:10.920 --> 11:12.922
Don't you want a balloon?

11:14.960 --> 11:17.804
I'm not supposed to take stuff
from strangers.

11:17.960 --> 11:19.007
My dad said so.

11:19.720 --> 11:23.725
Very wise of your dad, Georgie.
Very wise indeed.

11:24.760 --> 11:28.765
I, Georgie, am Pennywvise,
the Dancing Clown.

11:29.640 --> 11:31.688
You are Georgie.

11:32.600 --> 11:34.125
So, now we know each other.

11:34.920 --> 11:35.921
Correct?

11:36.400 --> 11:37.845
I guess so.

11:38.040 --> 11:39.610
- I've got to go.
<i>- Go?</i>

11:40.040 --> 11:42.042
Without this?

11:43.280 --> 11:45.886
- My boat!
- Exactly.

11:46.280 --> 11:49.284
Go on, kiddo. Take it.

11:52.080 --> 11:53.241
Oh...

11:54.400 --> 11:56.482
You want it, don't you, Georgie?

11:56.960 --> 11:58.689
<i>Of course you do.</i>

11:59.360 --> 12:03.809
And there's cotton candy and rides
and all sorts of surprises down here.

12:04.240 --> 12:07.005
And balloons, too. All colors.

12:07.600 --> 12:10.365
- Do they float?
- Oh, yes.

12:11.600 --> 12:14.649
They float, Georgie.

12:15.800 --> 12:17.165
They float.

12:19.080 --> 12:22.323
And when you're down here with me,

12:22.480 --> 12:24.960
you float, too!

12:29.200 --> 12:31.248
"Fear no evil for thou art with me,

12:31.520 --> 12:33.727
"thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me.

12:34.280 --> 12:38.001
"Thou preparest a table before me
in the presence of mine enemies.

12:38.160 --> 12:42.131
"Thou anointest my head with oil,
my cup runneth over.

12:42.360 --> 12:46.206
"Surely goodness and mercy
shall follow me all the days of my life.

12:46.360 --> 12:49.842
<i>"And I will dwell
in the house of the Lord forever."</i>

13:29.800 --> 13:31.086
Oh, Georgie.

13:39.560 --> 13:40.561
No.

13:54.400 --> 13:55.401
<i>Billy?</i>

13:55.760 --> 13:58.809
- Billy, are you all right?
- What's wrong, son? What is it?

13:59.000 --> 14:01.606
The picture. Georgie's picture.

14:04.360 --> 14:05.850
Mom, don't you see?

14:09.160 --> 14:10.161
<i>Mom.</i>

14:10.320 --> 14:13.802
- What were you doing in Georgie's room?
- Nothing.

14:13.960 --> 14:14.961
<i>Dad, listen!</i>

14:15.160 --> 14:18.403
I don't want you ever coming
in here again, son. Do you understand?

14:19.920 --> 14:21.604
- Dad.
- I mean it, Bill.

14:51.480 --> 14:52.641
I forgot.

14:54.120 --> 14:55.360
How could I forget?

14:56.440 --> 15:00.604
Leave? Have you lost your mind?
We're in the middle of making a movie.

15:00.760 --> 15:03.684
They can replace me.
This is something I have to do.

15:06.040 --> 15:07.963
Who was that on the phone?

15:10.680 --> 15:13.126
The call was from a guy named Mike Hanlon.

15:13.480 --> 15:16.802
I haven't heard from him in almost
30 years. Not since we were kids.

15:17.200 --> 15:21.205
- Audra. My brother, who died...
- Yes, George.

15:22.120 --> 15:23.645
He didn't just die.

15:23.920 --> 15:26.685
He was... Murdered.

15:27.160 --> 15:29.162
- Why didn't you ever...
- Tell you?

15:29.480 --> 15:33.804
Because I forgot. Because I forgot.
Almost as if it never happened.

15:33.960 --> 15:35.962
I know this doesn't make any sense,
but I have to go.

15:36.160 --> 15:37.366
For God's sake, why?

15:37.520 --> 15:40.171
Because we made a... promise.

15:40.320 --> 15:41.401
Why are you stuttering like that?

15:41.560 --> 15:44.006
I don't know.
I used to stutter when I was a kid.

15:44.160 --> 15:46.686
What happened? Tell me.

15:46.880 --> 15:49.690
Damn it, Bill, talk to me! Let me help.

15:51.280 --> 15:54.011
- If you're going back, I'm going, too.
- Don't even think that!

15:54.160 --> 15:57.050
- Why not? You're scaring me.
- You promise me you'll stay here.

15:57.200 --> 15:58.565
- Promise me!
- You're crazy.

15:58.720 --> 16:01.041
This is crazy.
Pro...

16:01.360 --> 16:02.725
It's just crazy.

16:05.560 --> 16:07.562
I love you.

16:45.000 --> 16:47.606
- Oops.
- Oh, no, Ben.

16:47.760 --> 16:51.207
Your architect award.
And you just received it. It's a tragedy.

16:51.400 --> 16:54.449
Yeah, honey.
We've got ourselves a real tragedy here.

16:54.600 --> 16:57.046
This is an American tragedy.

16:57.600 --> 16:59.921
Oh, look at this.
Would you hang on to this?

17:00.480 --> 17:02.289
I got this, and this, all right.

17:02.800 --> 17:04.768
- Okay.
- Come on.

17:06.600 --> 17:08.921
Here you are, my good man. Recycle.

17:09.920 --> 17:12.890
Here, wait a minute.
I got my magic, uh, opener.

17:13.800 --> 17:15.450
Come on, honey.

17:15.800 --> 17:18.804
Oh! Limbo! How low can you go?

17:19.000 --> 17:20.126
Whoo!

17:26.280 --> 17:28.442
No, no, no. You don't have to be quiet.

17:28.840 --> 17:31.207
- Is, is all this yours?
- Uh-huh. Come on in.

17:31.400 --> 17:33.402
Here, let me see what I can do with this.

17:33.600 --> 17:34.761
- Oh...
- Oops.

17:36.000 --> 17:37.650
It's so nice.

17:57.920 --> 18:00.924
Come here, beautiful. Come on.

18:01.880 --> 18:03.450
God, look at you!

18:04.840 --> 18:06.330
Ooh

18:06.920 --> 18:09.924
- I love your body.
- Ooh, I like yours, too.

18:10.280 --> 18:13.523
- Would you believe I used to be fat?
- I bet you were real cute.

18:13.680 --> 18:16.365
No, not just fat,
but a regular butterball.

18:16.680 --> 18:17.806
You bet your fern I was.

18:18.080 --> 18:19.525
We used to say that as kids.

18:19.720 --> 18:22.849
You bet your fern, but I was F-A-T.

18:23.240 --> 18:24.685
- No.
- Yeah.

18:29.720 --> 18:32.326
I hear bells. I'll be right back.

18:36.160 --> 18:37.161
Hello?

18:37.320 --> 18:38.970
<i>Haystack, it's me, Mike.</i>

18:40.040 --> 18:41.087
<i>You're dead, fat boy.</i>

18:42.080 --> 18:43.969
It's payback time, piggy.

18:45.440 --> 18:47.044
<i>You're gonna die, fat boy.</i>

18:47.200 --> 18:48.201
<i>Hey, fat boy!</i>

18:52.360 --> 18:53.361
<i>Ben?</i>

18:53.520 --> 18:54.885
<i>Ben, are you there?</i>

18:56.400 --> 18:58.721
- Mike?
<i>- Yeah, buddy. Listen.</i>

18:59.280 --> 19:01.760
<i>It... It's come back.</i>

19:04.360 --> 19:06.249
<i>How much do you remember?</i>

19:07.880 --> 19:09.882
<i>How much do you remember?</i>

19:11.920 --> 19:15.447
Very little. Almost nothing.

19:15.600 --> 19:17.284
<i>Will you come?</i>

19:19.440 --> 19:20.805
I'll come.

19:38.920 --> 19:40.046
Are you okay?

19:40.480 --> 19:44.485
I don't think I am, sweetheart.
Not tonight. Not at all.

19:46.000 --> 19:47.570
Are you gonna kill yourself?

19:48.480 --> 19:52.246
No, I don't think so.
Though it might be better if I did.

20:29.120 --> 20:31.930
<i>My name is Ben Hanscom.</i>

20:33.320 --> 20:36.563
Until last week,
I lived with my mom in Houston, Texas.

20:37.520 --> 20:39.488
<i>We moved here to live with my cousins.</i>

20:39.640 --> 20:41.085
Look at that gut.

20:44.680 --> 20:45.681
Go on, Ben.

20:46.360 --> 20:47.885
Have you any hobbies?

20:48.120 --> 20:49.360
Well, I like to read a lot.

20:49.640 --> 20:54.601
<i>Especially about old civilizations,
the Egyptians, the Indians.</i>

20:54.840 --> 20:58.925
We have a wonderful library here, Ben.
Welcome to Derry.

20:59.120 --> 21:01.122
Thank you, Miss Douglas.
Oink, oink.

21:12.800 --> 21:13.961
What a porker.

21:15.600 --> 21:17.045
Henry Bowers,

21:17.200 --> 21:20.204
you will stay for one hour after school
every day this week.

21:20.360 --> 21:21.885
My father will tan my hide.

21:22.040 --> 21:24.566
You should've thought of that
before you picked on Ben.

21:24.880 --> 21:26.882
<i>Now, report to the principal's office.</i>

21:33.000 --> 21:34.081
You're dead, fat boy.

21:41.240 --> 21:44.881
Boy. It's going to be
some funeral, friend.

21:54.520 --> 21:55.885
Now, class,

21:56.320 --> 22:01.451
as you know, the sheriff
00 p.m. curfew.

22:01.600 --> 22:04.001
<i>We live in dangerous times,
boys and girls.</i>

22:04.160 --> 22:06.561
<i>I want you to be careful.</i>

22:13.800 --> 22:16.804
Like this place so well
you're going to stand there all day?

22:16.960 --> 22:17.961
School's over, you know.

22:18.120 --> 22:20.248
- Excuse us, please.
- Can we get through?

22:20.440 --> 22:22.761
Honestly, Loni, some people have no class.

22:22.920 --> 22:24.922
Some people have janitors for parents.

22:29.160 --> 22:32.130
Well, so long, Ben Hanscom.

22:32.680 --> 22:34.364
I'm Beverly Marsh.

22:38.560 --> 22:40.608
Well, see you tomorrow, Beverly Marsh.

22:40.760 --> 22:45.402
Beverly Marsh. Beverly Marsh.
Beverly Marsh. Beverly Marsh.

22:50.200 --> 22:53.727
- Hey, look, it's the fat boy.
- Top of the day, fat boy.

23:03.200 --> 23:05.407
- What do you want?
- I want to teach you something, porky.

23:05.560 --> 23:06.766
You like to learn new things, don't you?

23:07.480 --> 23:09.084
Mmm-hmm.

23:09.600 --> 23:11.090
I want to make sure you remember my name.

23:11.480 --> 23:13.005
I'll remember, Henry. I'll remember.

23:13.200 --> 23:14.770
How am I gonna make sure? Huh?

23:20.400 --> 23:21.401
Hey, Henry.

23:22.480 --> 23:23.720
Come on, don't really cut him.

23:23.920 --> 23:25.251
Cut him? Huh?

23:26.200 --> 23:27.201
Cut him?

23:28.440 --> 23:30.568
Let's see, first comes...

23:30.760 --> 23:31.761
Oh, God!

23:34.840 --> 23:37.889
<i>You're going to die! You're dead!
I'm gonna bury you!</i>

23:38.040 --> 23:39.530
You're going to die!

23:41.000 --> 23:42.843
<i>I'm gonna bury you!</i>

23:49.520 --> 23:51.204
<i>Nobody kicks me, porky!</i>

23:51.480 --> 23:54.006
<i>Nobody kicks me! Nobody!
Come on, fat boy.</i>

23:54.280 --> 23:55.645
<i>You better run, boy.</i>

23:55.800 --> 23:57.325
<i>You're going to die, man!</i>

23:57.520 --> 24:00.683
<i>Come on, let's get him!
You're dead, fat pig!</i>

24:08.080 --> 24:10.560
<i>Hey, what's this?</i>

24:10.800 --> 24:12.802
<i>Looks like
a geek wading pool to me.</i>

24:18.800 --> 24:20.768
So what are you two girls
doing down here?

24:20.920 --> 24:24.322
Hey, look at the dam,
a stupid little baby dam.

24:29.560 --> 24:31.961
You didn't have to do that.
Why did you do that?

24:32.120 --> 24:34.009
'Cause I felt like it. Give me that.

24:34.200 --> 24:37.170
- That's for my asthma.
- Oh, is that a fact, sissy?

24:40.040 --> 24:42.566
- Leave him alone.
- Shut up, you little creep.

24:44.640 --> 24:47.246
I said stop that,

24:47.400 --> 24:50.927
<i>or I'll pull your ears down
and tie them underneath your chin.</i>

24:51.400 --> 24:53.448
- You seen a fat kid run by here?
- No.

24:53.600 --> 24:56.046
<i>Big, fat kid, all messed up.
No.</i>

24:56.200 --> 24:59.249
<i>You sure, mush-mouth?
You better be sure.</i>

24:59.400 --> 25:00.970
<i>I'm sure.</i>

25:01.760 --> 25:02.761
Let's go.

25:04.640 --> 25:07.291
Ta-ta, girls.

25:15.080 --> 25:16.491
Oh, no.

25:17.280 --> 25:18.611
It's empty-

25:23.160 --> 25:25.162
I can't breathe.

25:27.440 --> 25:28.771
Are they gone?

25:29.760 --> 25:32.411
Yes. Look, can you stay here
with my friend

25:32.560 --> 25:34.130
while I go get his medicine?

25:34.440 --> 25:35.441
Yeah.

25:35.600 --> 25:37.011
Here. Eddie, it's okay.

25:38.360 --> 25:39.646
Take it easy, kid. You'll be okay.

25:41.360 --> 25:43.522
- You'll be okay.
- Yeah?

25:43.840 --> 25:46.923
What are we gonna do if...
They come back?

25:53.280 --> 25:54.361
Want some?

25:59.800 --> 26:02.804
- My dad, he died of the big "C".
- "The big 'C'"?

26:02.960 --> 26:05.440
Cancer. I was just a little kid.

26:05.600 --> 26:08.843
Yeah, my dad died, too.
He was shot down in Korea.

26:09.040 --> 26:13.489
- Remember him much?
- Sort of, I think.

26:15.480 --> 26:17.608
- So, who's the other guy?
- Bill?

26:17.800 --> 26:21.600
Bill's my best friend.
He's a really great guy.

26:22.480 --> 26:23.481
<i>Hey!</i>

26:24.080 --> 26:25.081
I'm

26:25.840 --> 26:26.841
back.

26:28.760 --> 26:31.843
- Does he always stutter that much?
- It's worse since his kid brother died.

26:32.000 --> 26:33.365
Some guy killed George.

26:33.520 --> 26:36.251
Pulled one of his arms right off,
just like a wing off a fly.

26:36.400 --> 26:37.481
That's awful.

26:37.640 --> 26:40.166
I just told you because
if you want Bill to be your friend,

26:40.320 --> 26:42.129
it's better not to talk to him
about George.

26:42.280 --> 26:45.204
- He's all messed up about it.
- Man, I would be, too.

26:45.680 --> 26:48.843
"Would be, too," what?
- Oh, nothing. Thanks.

26:49.040 --> 26:50.041
Yeah.

26:50.200 --> 26:51.281
Thanks for staying.

26:51.440 --> 26:52.885
Jeez. He's really got it bad.

26:53.040 --> 26:56.442
I was scared he's going to
slip into a coma like on <i>Dr. Kildare.</i>

26:56.600 --> 27:01.731
- Me, too. You're Ben.
- Yeah, and you're Bill.

27:01.880 --> 27:06.602
- Yeah, and this is...
- Eddie. He knows.

27:06.760 --> 27:09.604
I hate it when you stutter my name, Bill.
You sound like Elmer Fudd.

27:09.760 --> 27:10.807
Sorry.

27:10.960 --> 27:14.601
No, no, no. No, Elmer Fudd has a lisp.
It's Porky Pig that stutters.

27:14.760 --> 27:16.285
Okay, Okay-

27:16.480 --> 27:18.562
- Why don't you come back tomorrow?
- Yeah.

27:19.040 --> 27:22.408
Me and Eddie, we're trying to make a dam.

27:22.960 --> 27:24.405
Well, you gotta have some boards.

27:24.560 --> 27:26.881
You get boards and you put them in a row,
facing each other.

27:27.080 --> 27:29.890
Like the bread of a sandwich and then...
But we...

27:30.360 --> 27:31.566
Huh?

27:32.040 --> 27:34.725
- But we do it.
- Oh, yeah, "we."

27:54.640 --> 27:57.086
- What are you doing, coz?
- Just something for school.

27:57.240 --> 27:58.287
Let's see.

27:58.600 --> 28:01.126
- Ooh. A poem.
- That's private.

28:01.440 --> 28:02.930
"Your hair is winter fire.

28:03.320 --> 28:05.129
"January embers."

28:05.440 --> 28:07.363
Hey, Mom, listen to this, Benny's in love!

28:07.520 --> 28:08.567
Give this back.

28:08.920 --> 28:12.367
Oh, Mom! Mom!
- Stop that! Benjamin!

28:12.520 --> 28:16.445
Hanscom, stop that immediately,
you young ruffian!

28:16.600 --> 28:17.601
I hate you!

28:17.800 --> 28:20.804
You're only here because
Mom says it's our Christian duty.

28:26.240 --> 28:28.641
<i>Nobody's ever going to say
a sister of mine is on welfare.</i>

28:28.800 --> 28:31.007
So you're welcome here
as long as you need to stay.

28:31.160 --> 28:33.481
But I have to say
you're spoiling the boy, Arlene.

28:33.640 --> 28:35.483
You need a firm hand, discipline.

28:47.640 --> 28:50.086
We'll have a home of our own
one day, Benny. I promise.

28:50.240 --> 28:51.571
I know, Mama.

28:52.080 --> 28:55.801
Benny, as long as we're guests
in this house, I need you to help me.

28:56.200 --> 28:58.851
They wouldn't treat us like this
if Daddy were still alive.

28:59.000 --> 29:00.331
Come on inside now and apologize.

29:00.480 --> 29:01.811
Apologize? But he was...

29:01.960 --> 29:06.090
- Benny, you must!
- No! I hate it here. I hate it here.

29:06.240 --> 29:07.765
Benny, come on. Benny.

29:09.480 --> 29:10.845
<i>Benny!</i>

29:31.440 --> 29:34.250
<i>Ben! Benny! Up here, Ben.</i>

29:34.880 --> 29:35.881
Daddy?

29:36.960 --> 29:37.961
<i>Benny!</i>

29:41.080 --> 29:42.081
<i>Ben!</i>

29:44.120 --> 29:45.121
<i>Ben!</i>

29:46.880 --> 29:47.881
<i>Hi, Ben.</i>

29:53.440 --> 29:54.487
Daddy?

29:55.840 --> 29:57.808
That's my home now, son.

30:00.600 --> 30:02.125
Do you want a balloon, Ben?

30:03.720 --> 30:05.290
They float.

30:06.240 --> 30:07.241
They all float.

30:08.560 --> 30:11.370
Come here, son. You'll like it down there.

30:12.080 --> 30:13.366
You'll never have to grow up.

30:29.800 --> 30:31.609
They float.

30:31.760 --> 30:33.808
They all float.

30:33.960 --> 30:36.247
And when you're down here with me,

30:36.520 --> 30:40.605
<i>fat boy, you'll float, too.</i>

30:48.800 --> 30:50.040
Please.

30:54.080 --> 30:56.242
Please, stop.

31:01.600 --> 31:04.570
Beverly By Hand. One moment, please.

31:08.280 --> 31:09.805
Miss Marsh's office.

31:10.400 --> 31:12.323
Hold a moment, please.

31:19.480 --> 31:21.642
Bev, someone calling from Maine,
says it's important.

31:21.800 --> 31:22.801
Maine?

31:22.960 --> 31:26.043
- Pam, I said no calls until...
- We've got a minute. I'll take it.

31:26.320 --> 31:29.051
No. Get their number and close the door.

31:43.480 --> 31:45.209
Your hands are shaking.

31:45.760 --> 31:47.171
I'm scared to death, Tom.

31:48.240 --> 31:51.289
That stuff spreads like cancer.
I won't have it around.

31:52.080 --> 31:53.081
Ah.

31:53.480 --> 31:55.687
There. That's perfect. Don't touch it.

31:56.960 --> 31:58.041
Listen to me, Bevy.

31:58.880 --> 32:00.962
We've got a bunch
of well-heeled Japanese gentlemen

32:01.120 --> 32:02.565
waiting for us downstairs.

32:02.960 --> 32:04.007
We're gonna show 'em around.

32:04.160 --> 32:06.891
You're gonna play
the charming flamboyant designer.

32:07.040 --> 32:08.405
We're gonna sit down, make a deal,

32:08.560 --> 32:11.166
I'm gonna play hardball,
and when it's over, we're gonna be rich.

32:11.720 --> 32:14.371
If you get a hold of yourself right now.

32:14.600 --> 32:15.965
- Do you understand?
- Mmm-hmm.

32:16.680 --> 32:18.205
Okay. Kiss for good luck?

32:25.400 --> 32:26.447
Okay, let's go.

32:26.600 --> 32:30.321
And Bevy, don't ever contradict me
in front of Pam again, okay?

32:31.840 --> 32:32.841
Okay.

32:53.800 --> 32:56.167
Good afternoon, gentlemen.
I'm Beverly Marsh.

32:56.320 --> 32:58.243
This is my partner, Tom Rogan.

33:34.720 --> 33:37.451
Hello?
<i>Beverly, it's Mike Hanlon.</i>

33:37.680 --> 33:39.921
- Who?
<i>- Mike Hanlon- Remember me?</i>

33:40.120 --> 33:43.761
Mike Hanlon. Of course I remember.
How are you?

33:43.920 --> 33:45.729
<i>Fine. Look, are you sitting down?</i>

33:52.120 --> 33:53.485
There you are.

33:58.280 --> 33:59.327
Whoa.

34:08.880 --> 34:10.211
Who was on the phone?

34:18.400 --> 34:20.801
I know you're going to think
this is crazy...

34:20.960 --> 34:22.724
I certainly think it's crazy,

34:22.880 --> 34:24.484
but I've gotta go to Maine.

34:25.160 --> 34:26.764
It's... It's hard to explain. Um...

34:27.320 --> 34:30.449
That was Mike Hanlon on the phone.
You remember the call at work today?

34:30.600 --> 34:32.364
He's an old, dear friend. I have to...

34:32.520 --> 34:35.251
Shut up! That's what you have to do,
just shut up!

34:35.400 --> 34:37.482
The very day I make a deal
of a lifetime for you,

34:37.640 --> 34:39.768
<i>you wanna run off to Maine
with some old boyfriend?</i>

34:40.040 --> 34:41.849
What do you take me for?

34:42.440 --> 34:44.727
Oh, boy. I've seen this coming.

34:45.200 --> 34:48.443
Oh, yes. You've forgotten
your manners, little girl.

34:48.840 --> 34:51.844
Contradicting me here,
smarting off there, and now this.

34:54.360 --> 34:56.522
You've forgotten your lessons, Bevy.

34:57.680 --> 34:59.762
It's been too long since last time.

35:00.200 --> 35:01.770
Put that thing down.

35:02.360 --> 35:04.522
I have to get out to O'Hare
as fast as I can.

35:05.760 --> 35:09.207
There's some trouble,
some very bad trouble.

35:09.480 --> 35:13.849
<i>It's come back, Beverly.
It's come back. Remember your promise.</i>

35:14.520 --> 35:16.522
- Put these clothes back.
- No.

35:16.680 --> 35:18.523
- You get into bed!
- No!

35:19.280 --> 35:20.884
Then maybe you can
leave this house in two days...

35:21.040 --> 35:22.849
- No!
- ...instead of two weeks.

35:23.000 --> 35:26.766
Not ever, ever, ever again!

35:36.560 --> 35:40.326
Listen to me. If you ever come
near me again, I will kill you.

35:40.480 --> 35:44.201
Do you understand? I will kill you.

35:46.080 --> 35:47.844
Bev, you need me!

35:48.200 --> 35:49.725
Bev!

36:03.800 --> 36:04.926
O'Hare, please.

36:05.160 --> 36:06.241
What airline, miss?

36:07.560 --> 36:09.562
Uh...

36:10.240 --> 36:12.083
I, uh, I need to go to Maine.

36:12.240 --> 36:14.925
All right. We'll find one
that goes to Maine.

36:15.080 --> 36:16.809
What's in Maine? Family?

36:17.640 --> 36:19.130
Friends.

36:20.080 --> 36:21.764
The best I ever had.

36:22.600 --> 36:24.284
Daddy, breakfast is ready.

36:26.040 --> 36:27.280
I'll get it.

36:51.240 --> 36:52.969
"Your hair is winter fire.

36:54.320 --> 36:55.651
"January embers.

36:56.720 --> 36:58.768
"My heart burns there, too."

36:58.920 --> 37:00.649
Who was that at the door, Bevy?

37:01.360 --> 37:02.805
- What do you got there?
- Nothing.

37:02.960 --> 37:03.961
Let me see that.

37:07.800 --> 37:09.086
You been doing something you shouldn't?

37:10.400 --> 37:13.609
You been fooling around with some boy?
Poetry from some boy?

37:16.960 --> 37:18.564
I worry about you a lot, Bevy.

37:18.840 --> 37:21.320
- Sometimes, I worry a lot.
- Daddy, please.

37:22.160 --> 37:25.528
Not even 12
and already running with some boy.

37:25.720 --> 37:27.324
Let me alone, you just let me alone!

37:27.480 --> 37:28.481
Come here!

37:29.440 --> 37:32.683
Don't make me go over there
and collect you. You come to me.

37:32.840 --> 37:33.841
No.

37:34.000 --> 37:36.810
- What did you say?
- I said no!

37:41.680 --> 37:43.887
You get right the hell back here, Bevy!

37:44.080 --> 37:47.402
And in front of God,
I'll whip the skin off of you!

38:04.320 --> 38:05.321
<i>Hi.</i>

38:07.040 --> 38:09.361
I'm sorry if I scared you. Are you okay?

38:09.920 --> 38:10.967
Yeah.

38:16.560 --> 38:19.564
Haven't you got anything better to do
than go sneaking up on people?

38:22.120 --> 38:24.851
- Sorry.
- You should be.

38:26.120 --> 38:28.805
Well, I was thinking,
it being Saturday and all,

38:28.960 --> 38:30.803
and if you didn't have
anything better to do,

38:30.960 --> 38:32.883
you could come down with me
to the barrens.

38:34.200 --> 38:35.531
The barrens?

38:37.280 --> 38:38.645
This is Eddie,

38:39.240 --> 38:40.765
<i>and this is Bill.</i>

38:43.400 --> 38:44.526
Hi.

38:46.240 --> 38:47.605
Hi.

38:49.560 --> 38:51.562
Do you guys know each other already?

38:54.920 --> 38:58.891
Well, Bev wants to help. I hope it's okay.
I mean, she's a girl.

39:00.240 --> 39:01.241
Sure.

39:02.760 --> 39:05.525
Hey, what's this? By George, Martha,

39:05.680 --> 39:07.409
it's the river Nile.

39:07.600 --> 39:10.285
And four, count them, four sphinxes.

39:10.720 --> 39:11.721
Richie.

39:12.280 --> 39:13.884
You were expecting maybe Gunga Din?

39:14.440 --> 39:17.250
That's Richie. He can drive you
to the bughouse and back, but he's okay.

39:17.440 --> 39:21.604
I heard that, you skirt. Hi, Bill.
How you doin', Eddie Spaghetti?

39:22.080 --> 39:25.607
Don't do that. I hate it when you do that.
And don't call me "Eddie Spaghetti."

39:26.000 --> 39:28.526
Oh, you love it, Eddie.
It's what makes you so chuck-a-licious.

39:28.720 --> 39:29.721
Richie Tozier's my name.

39:32.280 --> 39:35.568
And doing voices is my game.
This is Stan "the Man" Uris.

39:35.720 --> 39:38.485
Stannie's a Jew, which means
he's really smart and says <i>"oy"</i> a lot.

39:38.640 --> 39:41.803
Richie's got a high metabolism,
and it tends to make him hyperactive.

39:42.160 --> 39:45.050
So you, um, Haystack,
what, are you building a dam or something?

39:45.200 --> 39:46.247
Yeah.

39:46.440 --> 39:48.204
- You ever built one before?
- No.

39:48.600 --> 39:49.647
How do you know it'll work?

39:50.120 --> 39:52.646
- Well, of course it will. Why wouldn't it?
- Yeah, but how do you know?

39:52.800 --> 39:53.801
I just know.

39:53.960 --> 39:55.803
- Yeah, he just knows.
- Yeah.

39:55.960 --> 39:57.041
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

39:57.360 --> 39:58.361
Well,okay.

40:28.000 --> 40:30.367
- You're a genius, Haystack.
- Oh, it's not so much.

40:30.520 --> 40:33.205
- Yes, it is. It's great.
- We stopped that sucker cold!

40:33.360 --> 40:34.361
- Yeah.
- It's great.

40:34.520 --> 40:36.727
We could flood out the whole barrens
if we wanted to.

40:36.880 --> 40:38.769
We did it! We!

40:38.920 --> 40:40.843
- Yes!
- Yeah! Yeah!

40:46.520 --> 40:48.682
Listen, I'll go this way.

40:50.000 --> 40:52.606
- See you later, alligator.
- After a while, crocodile.

40:55.040 --> 40:57.725
- See you, Ben.
- Yeah, see you, Bill.

40:58.560 --> 41:01.450
Hi yo, Silver. Away!

41:04.160 --> 41:05.571
See you, Beverly.

41:05.760 --> 41:06.886
See you.

41:17.720 --> 41:19.404
My heart burns there, too.

41:29.440 --> 41:33.843
77 Sunset Strip <i>will continue
following station identification.</i>

41:39.920 --> 41:41.331
<i>Help me.</i>

41:42.400 --> 41:44.607
<i>Help me, please.</i>

41:46.960 --> 41:48.166
<i>Help me.</i>

41:50.240 --> 41:52.641
<i>- Help me, Beverly.</i>
- Hello?

41:54.440 --> 41:55.441
Is someone there?

41:55.920 --> 41:59.811
<i>The clown brought us down here.
We all float.</i>

41:59.960 --> 42:01.007
Who are you?

42:01.440 --> 42:04.410
<i>I'm Vickie Burrows.
I'm Matthew O'Connor.</i>

42:04.720 --> 42:07.246
<i>We're all the dead kids.</i>

42:09.280 --> 42:13.001
<i>Come closer, Beverly.
We all want to meet you.</i>

42:13.280 --> 42:14.645
<i>We float.
We float.</i>

42:22.080 --> 42:23.081
Daddy!

42:23.800 --> 42:27.441
- What in the name of heaven?
- The bathroom, Daddy, the bathroom!

42:27.920 --> 42:31.003
- Was someone peeping in at you, girl?
- The sink, in the sink!

42:34.600 --> 42:38.047
Well, what is it you think you saw?
Speak up, girl!

42:40.480 --> 42:41.527
<i>I worry about you, Bevy.</i>

42:41.800 --> 42:43.643
Sometimes I worry a lot.

42:44.800 --> 42:46.370
Now explain yourself!

42:46.520 --> 42:50.923
There was a spider.
A big, fat spider.

42:51.160 --> 42:54.403
It crawled out of the drain,
and I guess it crawled back down again.

42:55.520 --> 42:57.363
Now, these buildings are old,

42:57.520 --> 42:59.329
<i>with drains the size
of the Holland Tunnel.</i>

42:59.800 --> 43:01.484
There's nothing there now.

43:06.200 --> 43:07.326
Get to bed.

43:10.680 --> 43:13.968
<i>Say hello to your friends, Beverly.</i>

43:15.680 --> 43:18.126
<i>You'll die if you try to fight us.</i>

43:19.960 --> 43:22.327
<i>You'll die if you try.</i>

43:22.920 --> 43:26.845
<i>You'll die
if you try to fight us, Beverly.</i>

43:27.360 --> 43:33.527
<i>You'll die if you try.</i>

43:34.200 --> 43:37.249
<i>You'll die if you try.</i>

43:37.520 --> 43:40.603
<i>You'll die if you try.</i>

43:41.040 --> 43:44.362
<i>You'll die if you try.</i>

43:53.760 --> 43:55.410
<i>Eddie!</i>

43:55.560 --> 43:57.403
<i>Eddie, where are you?</i>

44:00.120 --> 44:01.770
<i>Eddie?</i>

44:04.840 --> 44:08.208
<i>- Eddie, where are you?</i>
- I'm in here, Ma.

44:12.240 --> 44:13.241
Eddie.

44:13.960 --> 44:14.961
Ah.

44:16.560 --> 44:19.291
Where... Where are you going?

44:19.560 --> 44:21.050
I have to go away for a while.

44:21.200 --> 44:23.567
"Away"? Where?

44:24.240 --> 44:27.403
Eddie, this isn't like you.
Tell me where you're going.

44:27.600 --> 44:28.886
Eddie, stop!

44:30.040 --> 44:32.486
You're in trouble, aren't you?

44:32.920 --> 44:33.921
Eddie?

44:34.840 --> 44:38.242
Tell me who was on the phone. Answer me.

44:38.760 --> 44:39.966
Answer me.

44:40.440 --> 44:42.681
Mom, please, please. Don't cry, okay?

44:42.840 --> 44:46.128
Eddie, you're scaring me so bad,
you've got to tell me.

44:47.240 --> 44:48.241
Eddie.

44:49.800 --> 44:50.801
Eddie.

44:51.000 --> 44:54.322
- Where are you going? Derry?
- I've gotta go back to Derry.

44:55.440 --> 44:58.125
Why would you want to go back
to that dirty little town?

44:58.280 --> 45:01.284
There's nothing for you there.
There never was, Eddie.

45:02.800 --> 45:05.451
Please, Ma. Please.

45:08.280 --> 45:09.281
Eddie!

45:11.240 --> 45:14.244
- Let's get out of here.
- Jeez, Eddie.

45:14.640 --> 45:15.687
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

45:15.840 --> 45:17.888
- You look like you've seen a ghost.
- Move it!

45:19.640 --> 45:21.210
<i>Eddie!</i>

45:28.280 --> 45:30.647
Joey, I'm sorry
to be leaving you holding the bag.

45:30.800 --> 45:32.484
Do we have enough drivers
lined up for next week?

45:32.640 --> 45:33.641
It's covered, Eddie.

45:33.800 --> 45:36.280
All right, I want you to do
the Pacino job yourself.

45:36.440 --> 45:38.204
Remember, he likes the Lincoln stretch.

45:38.400 --> 45:40.562
I know, Eddie.
The business is under control.

45:40.720 --> 45:41.801
Great.

45:41.960 --> 45:45.089
It's you I'm worried about. Yeah?
I'm fine.

45:45.240 --> 45:46.480
So where are we going?

45:47.160 --> 45:50.562
30 to Boston.

46:58.640 --> 46:59.687
They saw me.

47:00.400 --> 47:03.529
- We... We better go.
- I'm a dead man.

47:03.680 --> 47:06.411
If I were you guys,
I wouldn't pay to see a monster movie,

47:06.560 --> 47:07.846
I'd just stay home and look in a mirror.

47:08.080 --> 47:09.081
Richie!

47:21.680 --> 47:23.125
Let's get out of here!

47:23.280 --> 47:24.611
Yeah, let's go!

47:26.320 --> 47:29.369
Oh, did you see those guys?
I saw you make it worse.

47:29.520 --> 47:31.443
Oh, come on, Eddie Spaghetti.

47:31.600 --> 47:34.888
It was just a joke.
Sometimes you joke too much.

47:35.080 --> 47:37.651
Yeah, well, sometimes you gotta
make jokes, or you die of boredom.

47:37.800 --> 47:41.168
I mean, are we men or are we mice?
We're mice!

47:41.320 --> 47:43.288
Then let's act like mice.

47:43.560 --> 47:44.561
Oh, look.

47:50.520 --> 47:53.763
That place scares me green.
I think it's haunted.

47:54.120 --> 47:57.363
Honestly, Eddie, such things
just aren't empirically possible.

47:57.560 --> 47:59.369
In English, ain't no such thing.

47:59.560 --> 48:03.201
You know, you're a pretty swift guy
for a girl, my little chickadee.

48:03.400 --> 48:07.325
Why, Richie Tozier, was that a compliment?
On our very first date?

48:07.720 --> 48:08.960
On...

48:09.240 --> 48:10.810
How come Richie's so special?

48:10.960 --> 48:14.043
Well, the date wasn't just with him,
Eddie dear. I love you, too.

48:14.480 --> 48:15.845
- Ooh.
- Ew.

48:29.480 --> 48:31.482
Hey, don't trip!

48:31.840 --> 48:33.330
Whoa!

48:43.000 --> 48:47.767
You know, Eddie,
it's been great, but see you later.

48:47.960 --> 48:49.610
See you later.
Bye, Eddie.

48:52.160 --> 48:55.243
I wish this summer would never end.
It's the best summer of my whole life.

48:55.400 --> 48:56.845
Eddie.

48:57.440 --> 48:59.408
Eddie Kaspbrak,

49:00.240 --> 49:03.164
I was worried sick.
I almost called the police.

49:03.320 --> 49:05.607
Eddie was with us, Mrs...
- Go away.

49:06.320 --> 49:07.367
<i>Go home.</i>

49:07.680 --> 49:09.444
Ma, these are my friends.

49:09.600 --> 49:12.524
- See you tomorrow, Eddie.
- Eddie has to rest tomorrow.

49:18.040 --> 49:20.884
I don't want you to play with them
anymore. No good will come of it.

49:21.040 --> 49:22.041
But, Ma, they're my friends.

49:22.200 --> 49:24.965
You don't need any friends, Eddie,
except for your own ma.

49:25.120 --> 49:27.043
<i>You feel warm.
I'm fine.</i>

49:27.200 --> 49:30.568
<i>No gym and no showers
with the other boys this week.</i>

49:30.720 --> 49:32.563
<i>I don't want you catching their germs.</i>

